cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep reinforcement learning-based technique for network quantization. It also involves the use of neural networks (CNNs) and optimization of their performance. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as CNNs are commonly used in computer vision tasks. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to optimize the performance of neural networks. Furthermore, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the optimization of neural networks. Lastly, it could be categorized under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it involves the optimization of hardware-friendly techniques for deploying CNNs on low-power mobile devices.
